<h5>Schwartzberg</h5>
<p>The Schwartzberg score (SS) compactness score is the ratio of the perimeter of the district (PD) to the circumference of a circle whose area is equal to the area of the district. A district’s Schwartzberg score as calculated below falls with the range of [0,1] and a score closer to 1 indicates a more compact district.</p>
