<h5>Reock Score</h5>
<p>The Reock Score (R) is the ratio of the area of the district AD to the area of a minimum bounding cirle (AMBC) that encloses the district’s geometry. A district’s Reock score falls within the range of [0,1] and a score closer to 1 indicates a more compact district.</p>
