<h5>Convex Hull</h5>
<p>The Convex Hull score is a ratio of the area of the district to the area of the minimum convex polygon that can encloses the district’s geometry. A district’s Convex Hull score falls within the range of [0,1] and a score closer to 1 indicates a more compact district.</p>
